### Description

Currently the `ResourceStatus` is exposed as an enum. Because of this there is no convenient way of interacting with the status in html templates since you can't access enums within the template.

```html
@if(resource.status() === ResourceStatus.Idle) { // There is no way convenient way to access ResourceStatus enum in the html 
// render some html when status is idle
}
```

### Proposed solution

expose the `ResourceStatus` as a union of string literal types.

`export type ResourceStatus = 'Idle' | 'Error' | 'Loading' | 'Reloading' | 'Resolved' | 'Local';`

This would allow for the following template syntax
```html
@if(resource.status() === 'Idle') {
// render some html when status is idle
}
```

### Alternatives considered

Allow templates to refer to imported ts enums.

